#Text=( ( WN ) )
#Text=Who is your inspiration ?
#Text=( ( SG ) )
#Text=When it comes to webcomics , my inspiration has to be Shen from Blue Chair , and it is also called Shen Comics now .
#Text=Then , The Awkward Yeti — Nick Seluk , then Sarah Andersen 's comics — Sarah 's Scribbles .
#Text=Yeah , those are pretty much it .
#Text=I only read the mainstream ones before I decided to start making my own , So I do n't have a long list .
#Text=[ Laughs ]
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Where did you upload your first comic ?
#Text=( ( SG ) ) Facebook .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Are you self-taught ?
#Text=( ( SG ) ) Yes !
#Text=For the most part , yeah .
#Text=I mean , I am studying animation design , but when it comes to drawing , I completely just taught myself .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) Do you discuss your ideas before penning them down ?
#Text=( ( SG ) ) With some people .
#Text=I have a couple of friends , I talk to sometimes , but for most ideas , no .
#Text=I just go for it .
#Text=Yeah .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What tools do you use to create your comics ?
#Text=( ( SG ) ) I draw in Adobe Photoshop , and I use a Wiacom tablet .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) I wanted to know what is your official website .
#Text=( ( SG ) ) I do n't have an official website but it is all over on Facebook or Instagram and even on Webtoons , but I do n't have a website yet , but I am planning to start one soon .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) What are some of your hobbies ?
#Text=( ( SG ) ) Oh , it is just drawing , animating .
#Text=I play football , basketball , but mostly just drawing and animating .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) There is one character in your comic , which is called as[ ... ]
#Text=Kabeer .
#Text=Why did you name him Kabeer ?
#Text=( ( SG ) ) So Kabeer is a religiously ambiguous name .
#Text=Kabeer is n't overly seen as a Hindu or a Muslim or anything .

#Text=So it is a middle point and I wanted to keep a character that everyone can relate to , not just someone who belongs to a certain religion . So for that ambiguity , that is why I came up with the name , plus I really like the name .
#Text=That was actually , probably the main reason .

#Text=( ( WN ) ) There is this comic which you have titled " Folow my dreams , son " , which was about a boy who wanted to become a footballer , but ends up getting a degree from FFS College of Engineering .
#Text=So were there some challenges with your ...
#Text=( ( SG ) ) Absolutely not !
#Text=My parents have been super supportive from the start .
#Text=Like they actually told me to leave studies and go for art because I was so passionate about art and design .
#Text=So I have had a very very smooth sailing so far .
#Text=No parental pressure at all .
#Text=It has been amazing , yeah .
#Text=( ( WN ) ) If you had something to tell to your younger self , about your webcomics , what would you tell ?
#Text=( ( SG ) ) Read more .
#Text=Right now I am reading a lot of different kinds of comics so I can look at different ways of story telling .
#Text=If I had done that earlier , maybe I could have , maybe , I do n't know , some stories could have turned out better .
#Text=When I look at some of my older comics , I feel like , ' Okay this could have been done a little better ' sometimes .
#Text=So , that 's it .
#Text=Otherwise nothing .
#Text=Like I said , I had a smooth life , I do n't give a f ...
